    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate for Ghost Ride the WHIP hinges on capitalizing on high-speed environments and favorable wind conditions to squeeze out every possible stolen base. **Corbin Carroll** (80.85) is our absolute anchor; he is in a prime spot against Pop, benefiting from a +6% platoon boost and a matchup against a catcher with a slow 1.88s exchange, making him the highest-upside play of the day for our SB-starved categories. Similarly, **Brice Turang** (66.23) earns his spot at the top of the lineup, where his elite lead-off efficiency is complemented by a generous +10% order bonus, even with the modest penalty for facing a catcher with a 1.89s pop time. **Mickey Moniak** (64.99) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (58.38) are significant beneficiaries of today\u2019s weather, with favorable winds providing a performance lift that keeps their bats in the lineup despite challenging pitching matchups.\n\nThe rotation decisions remain disciplined, though **Zach McKinstry** (49.24) was the most difficult exclusion from the starting nine. While **Zach McKinstry** received a healthy boost due to Alcantara\u2019s slow delivery\u2014offering a prime target for a steal\u2014he was ultimately edged out by the superior raw efficiency of **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (59.07) and the high-order stability of **Austin Riley** (61.42). We are exercising caution with **James Wood** (51.64), whose start is predicated almost entirely on his 100% stolen base probability against Woodruff; should that matchup fail to yield early traffic, he remains the most volatile component of today\u2019s output. We are closely monitoring **Dalton Rushing** (42.63), who remains in the lineup despite a tough draw against deGrom; while the wind helps his profile, his score sits near our floor, making him a primary candidate for a mid-game pivot if the game script turns negative.",
